RACE.FOOTNOTES: MY KIKI had speed three wide then vied between rivals under rating mid turn, was roused clear approaching the quarter pole, widened a bit near mid stretch, kept on on under left handed asks inside the sixteenth pole then lasted over a charging BE A BANDIT. BE A BANDIT , urged in the clear and off of a contested early pace, swung five wide into the lane, leveled off when switching over to her correct lead near the sixteenth pole, closed gamely and simply ran out of ground. PEACEFUL VISION forced the pace between rivals into the turn, chased past the five sixteenths, shifted in and kept on with some interest. LAURIEANN bobbled at the break, was hustled up inside soon after to contest the p[ace, eased back off the leaders mid turn, came out for room bothering foes entering the lane, chased and faded. BLONDIE LOX BABE was shuffled back near the five and a half furlong marker, saved ground into the stretch and lacked a bid. PRINCESS TRINA flashed speed, angled out into the turn, moved up four wide nearing the quarter pole, was carried out by YOUNMEHONEYBUNNY after that one was floated out by LAURIEANN and weakened. YOUNMEHONEYBUNNY was rated back from between rivals early, bid four deep into the turn, pressed three wide mid turn, was carried out some by LAURIEANN soon into the stretch and gave way. Following an objection by the rider of PRINCESS TRINA against LAURIEANN, LAURIEANN was disqualified from fourth and placed sixth for causing interference entering the stretcn.
